        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 9 at 3:25PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sheldon, or near Channelview, moving west at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Northwestern Pasadena, Bellaire, West University Place, Galena Park,
Jacinto City, Hunters Creek Village, Bunker Hill Village, Piney Point
Village, Cloverleaf, Downtown Houston, Greenway / Upper Kirby Area,
Spring Branch North, Second Ward, Greater Heights, Neartown /
Montrose, Barrett, Memorial Park, Fourth Ward, Macgregor, and Midtown
Houston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
